##Wuhan Epidemic "WHISTLE-BLOWER" Li Wenliang: Every day to take antibiotics new pneumonia firsthand

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

Terence Chang contributed reporting from Wuhan

"today the nucleic acid test result is positive, the dust settles, finally diagnosed. " February 1 at 10:41 a.m. , the epidemic "whistle blower" Li Wenliang announced the news to the outside world. Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at Wuhan Central Hospital, was called a "whistle-blower" for the outbreak after he first alerted the outside world on December 30,2019.

On the afternoon of February 1, Li Wenliang told China business daily that he had promised his family to rest in peace and would not accept media interviews for the time being. He's being treated in isolation at Wuhan Central Hospital.

The day before, on January 31, the Beijing Gratitude Public Welfare Foundation allocated the first 100,000 yuan "special contribution support" since the foundation of the "Guardian Back Action" project, and the beneficiary was Li Wenliang. According to Zhou Jian, the head of the foundation, the money is mainly used to support those who have made outstanding contributions in the fight against the epidemic. "His actions have objectively enabled more people to take early precautions against the virus, " Zhou said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(Dr Lee man-leung, Wuhan Central Hospital)

Just a friendly reminder

Wuhan Central Hospital Back Lake Hospital area, is the closest to the south China Seafood Market, a straight line distance of not more than 1.5 km. Most of the first commercial patients infected with COVID-19 pneumonia came to the Lake District of Wuhan Central Hospital after treatment at nearby clinics and community hospitals failed to improve, this also allows doctors, including Li Wenliang, the first contact with patients, access to relevant diagnostic information.

As early as the afternoon of December 31,2019, the reporter had visited the back Lake Hospital area of the Wuhan Central Hospital. Several medical staff confirmed to the reporter that they had indeed admitted several suspected pneumonia patients last night (December 30) . It started on the first floor of the clinic in the emergency surgery ward, but it's been moved to the second floor. The reporter saw at that time on the first floor, the emergency surgical ward has closed the door, the door posted on the "door" notice.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(respiratory and critical care division, Back Lake District, Wuhan Central Hospital, photo taken on December 31,2019 by Terence Chang.)

"there were seven confirmed cases of SARS in the south China Seafood Market, " Li Wenliang recalled, announcing the news to the Wuhan University's clinical class of 2004 shortly after 5 p.m. on December 30,2019, remind the classmate of same clinician"let family member pay attention to guard against". Li Wenliang also became one of the first people to issue a protective warning to the outside world.

To prove his point, Li also sent out a copy of the clinical pathogen screening results and chest CT of the patient with "High Confidence Index positive for SARS coronavirus. ". An hour later, he added in the group: "The latest news is that the coronavirus infection has been confirmed and the virus typing is under way. "

On the same day, the Wuhan City Health Committee issued the "urgent notice on doing a good job in the treatment of pneumonia of unknown causes" began to circulate, pneumonia epidemic first into the public field of vision. The notice stressed in particular that "without authorization any unit, individuals shall not release rescue information to the outside. ".

After issuing a friendly warning to the students, Li Wenliang's work and life went on as usual. As an ophthalmologist, he was admitted to treat an 82-year-old patient with acute angle-closure Glaucoma and was exposed to the virus due to inadvertent exposure.

According to Li Wenliang description, about January 8, I admitted to the eye disease patients with normal body temperature, but poor appetite, and did not present new pneumonia common symptoms of fever. The next day or poor appetite, fever at noon, check the lung CT is "viral pneumonia" , other indicators are in line with the criteria for pneumonia of unknown cause.

On January 10,11, Li Wenliang presented with cough, fever and other symptoms; 12 because of fever, lung infection into the isolation ward, a suspected case, but has not been confirmed. He was later transferred to Wuhan General Hospital for Intensive-care Unit treatment.

It is understood that Li Wenliang currently breathing difficulties, inserted oxygen tube, can not get up, talk, through the typing and communication with others, "every day to play antibiotics, anti-virus, Globulin and oxygen. "

"Who dares to speak the truth. "

Li Wenliang is a 34-year-old native of Beizhen city, Jinzhou City, Liaoning Province. In 2004, Li Wenliang took the college entrance examination and applied for the Wuhan University seven-year program in clinical medicine. After working briefly in Xiamen for three years, he returned to Wuhan and has worked in Wuhan Central Hospital ever since, the course of working and living in Wuhan was opened.

"My wife is an ophthalmologist at another hospital and the child is only 5 years old. Now my wife is living with her child at her mother-in-law's home, " Li told the media, now every day and my lover Wechat Chat, video, they will give me encouragement.

The admitted OPHTHALMIC patient developed a "double lung ground glass lesion" after being diagnosed as a viral pneumonia patient. Her family and daughter, who cared for her, also developed fever. This reinforced Li's belief that "human-to-human transmission is evident, " but he did not continue to warn the outside world about it, for isolation or other reasons.

According to Li Wenliang in the "Caixin" interview, this is an obvious person to person. We immediately reported to the Medical Service and hospital office of the feeling, asked the hospital expert group consultation, after consultation patients in my ward isolation treatment. Three days later, we did a follow up CT, and it was still viral pneumonia, and it expanded, and it got worse, and then he was transferred to a suction isolation ward, and I don't know what happened after that.

After Li Wenliang developed fever and other symptoms, his colleagues in the same department also developed infection in the next day or two. His parents also developed fever and other symptoms three or four days later. The lung CT showed ground-glass Lesions and was hospitalized. According to Li Wenliang, they are being treated in other hospitals in Wuhan, are now quite good, no major problems, should be discharged in the near future.

According to the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission on January 11, the external caliber is still "no medical staff infection, no clear evidence of human-to-human transmission. ". "At that time I was wondering why the report still said there was no human-to-human transmission and no medical infection, " Li said.

It wasn't until the evening of January 20 that Zhong Nanshan, an academician at the Chinese Academy of Engineering and the Director of the respiratory disease, for the first time told the world that there must be human to human transmission of COVID-19, and disclosed the fact that "14 medical personnel are infected" .

Li Wenliang's deeds have also attracted the attention of public welfare organizations such as the Beijing Gratitude Public Welfare Foundation. At 21:00 on January 31, the foundation's "Guardian Back Action" program allocated the first 100,000 yuan "special contribution support" to Li Wenliang. The Rationale: He's a responsible, honest, and honest person who dares to tell the truth. His behavior objectively allowed more people to be on guard against the virus in advance.

According to Zhou, as of 21:00 on February 1, the staff and volunteers of the project team of Operation Guardian's backing are in contact with the 22 recipients or their families who initially met the funding conditions, they include 3 doctors, 8 medical staff, 9 police and auxiliary police officers and 2 cadres at the grass-roots level.

"Many of them have been heroes on the front lines of the epidemic, some have given their lives, some have been infected, some are still fighting, " said Operation Guardian, to provide free humanitarian assistance to all personnel (including not limited to medical and quarantine personnel, inspectors, journalists, etc.) involved in the fight against the "new type of pneumonia" in 2020 in the line of duty who become ill, become disabled or die in the line of duty, the contents of project support include living allowance, treatment support, education support, special pension, support for support and special contribution support.

"I will actively cooperate with the treatment and try to get out of the hospital as soon as possible, " Li said. After recovery, I would like to return to first-line work as soon as possible and continue to see patients.
